Serializable
public class ResourceAlreadyExistsException extends RuntimeException
Exception thrown when an attempt is made to create a resource that already exists.

This is a custom runtime exception used in the Expense Tracker application to indicate that a resource (such as a user, category, or transaction) cannot be created because it already exists in the system.

Usage Example:

 if (repository.existsByEmail(email)) {
        throw new ResourceAlreadyExistsException("User", "email", email);
 }

Constructors:

  • ResourceAlreadyExistsException() - Default constructor.
  • ResourceAlreadyExistsException(String, String, String) - For string-based identifiers.
  • ResourceAlreadyExistsException(String, String, Long) - For numeric identifiers.
  • ResourceAlreadyExistsException(String, String) - For generic resource and field names.
